com.kuka.roboticsAPI.sensorModel

Interface IDataRecorder

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RecordingService

    public interface IDataRecorder
    Enables recording of data in a file.

    Before recording, the IDataRecorder needs to be enabled. First, create a RecorderConfiguration using the RecorderConfigurator (see getConfigurator()). Then, enable the recorder and pass the configuration you created (see enable(RecorderConfiguration)).

    There are two options to use the IDataRecorder:

    1. In combination with a RobotMotion

    Here, the recording will be started by a trigger (StartRecordingAction), e.g.
    ".triggerWhen(ICondition, new StartRecordingAction(configuration))".

    Accordingly, it can be stopped by a trigger or after timeout (StopRecordingAction), e.g.
    ".triggerWhen(ICondition, new StopRecordingAction())".

    2. As stand-alone recording

    Here, the IDataRecorder can be started on command by calling "startRecording(RecorderConfiguration)". The recording can be stopped by timeout or by "stopRecording()".

    The recorded file is text based (csv-file) and is formated as a table with rows and columns. The first row contains a header which describes the values in each column. For each sample of the defined sample interval a row will be written which contains the recorded values of the added data sources. In the first and the second column the time stamp in nanoseconds is stored. Each additional column contains the parameterized data to record as described in the header. For example if recording Cartesian force (RecorderConfigurator.recordCartesianForce(Frame, Frame)), the file contains eight columns, the first and the second column for the time stamps and six columns for each value of the Cartesian force vector.

    • Method Detail

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Provides the state of the recording process.
        Returns:
        true if recording is enabled, false otherwise.

        true if the SPR-state of the data recording SPR is at least SPRState.PREPARING but not SPRState.MAINTAINING or further yet, false otherwise.

      • isRecording

        boolean isRecording()
        Provides the state of the recording process.
        Returns:
        true if recording process is active, false otherwise.

        true if the SPR-state of the data recording SPR is SPRState.ACTIVE, false otherwise.

      • enable

        void enable(RecorderConfiguration configuration)
        Enables the data recorder with the given recorder configuration.

        This does not start the recording process. Enabled means that the recorder is ready to start recording. A disable process occurs automatically when the recorder stops. This means that the same recorder must be enabled again in order to record data.

        Parameters:
        configuration - the recorder configuration to enable the data recorder with

      • startRecording

        void startRecording(RecorderConfiguration configuration)
        Starts recording using the given recorder configuration.

        In order to be able to start recording, this recorder needs to be enabled first (see enable(RecorderConfiguration)).

        Note that there is no guarantee about when precisely the recording will be started. If the recording should start at a specific point in time precisely, use the IDataRecorder with a trigger action (StartRecordingAction) instead.

        Parameters:
        configuration - the configuration to
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - in case the given configuration does not equal the configuration the data recorder was enabled with

      • stopRecording

        void stopRecording()
        Stops recording.

        Note that there is no guarantee about when precisely the recording will be stopped. If the recording should stop at a specific point in time precisely, use the IDataRecorder with a trigger action (StopRecordingAction) instead.

      • getConfiguration

        RecorderConfiguration getConfiguration()
        Returns the configuration.
      • If the recorder is enabled then the current configuration is returned.
      • If the recorder is not enabled then the previous configuration is returned.
      • If the recorder has no previous configuration then null is returned.
Returns:
the configuration

  • getConfigurator

    RecorderConfigurator getConfigurator()
    Returns the configurator connected to this data recorder. The configurator can be used to determine which data should be recorded by this recorder.

    To enable the recorder, use enable(RecorderConfiguration).

    Returns:
    the recorder configurator
